title: Data Model for PCF Session Management Policy - MediationZone Documentation 9.3 - InfoZone
text: Included in Development Toolkit User's Guide is an example of a data model for PCF Session Management Policy, as defined in: https://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/129500_129599/129512/16.08.00_60/ts_129512v160800p.pdf https://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/129500_129599/129571/15.03.00_60/ts_129571v150300p.pdf https://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/129200_129299/129212/15.03.00_60/ts_129212v150300p.pdf https://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/124000_124099/124008/13.07.00_60/ts_124008v130700p.pdf https://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/129500_129599/129514/17.05.00_60/ts_129514v170500p.pdf https://www.ieee802.org/802_tutorials/2013-03/8021-IETF-tutorial-final.pdf https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7042 In order to make full use of the SM Policy and create the needed business logic, it is important to understand the underlying data models. This section outlines the structure and underlying fields of each object in the data model, and contains the following sub sections: SMPolicy Data Model Common Data Model Provisioning PCF Session Management Policy in Desktop Online
